But I can't.

244
00:07:53,050 --> 00:07:54,110
It's not easy.

245
00:07:54,310 --> 00:07:55,849
It's hard for me to make a character for myself.

246
00:07:55,850 --> 00:07:56,979
- I want to be on many TV shows. - Right.

247
00:07:56,980 --> 00:07:58,579
I retired from being an athlete, and I want to pursue a new career.

248
00:07:58,580 --> 00:07:59,889
- But it's not easy. - Okay.

249
00:07:59,890 --> 00:08:02,119
So you're saying you don't think you can be like the two of them,

250
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,896
but you think you can reach Yeong Cheol's level.

251
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:06,089
- Yes, that's what it sounded like. - What does he mean...

252
00:08:06,090 --> 00:08:07,090
You think you can easily reach his level, right?

253
00:08:07,091 --> 00:08:09,359
- No. I respect Yeong Cheol. - I can't believe this.

254
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:11,329
- I mean it. Trust me. - It became complicated for me.

255
00:08:11,330 --> 00:08:12,369
No. I really mean it.

256
00:08:12,370 --> 00:08:13,799
Yeong Cheol is the only one...

257
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,229
- I'm following on social media. - But you know...

258
00:08:15,230 --> 00:08:17,139
- Listen to me. - I've been following him...

259
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:18,499
for a very long time.

260
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:19,569
- Oh, really? - But...

261
00:08:19,570 --> 00:08:21,039
- Then let me ask you a question. - Okay.

262
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:24,579
Sang Min always calls Min Soo "my dear big brother..."

263
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:27,049
- when he talks about Min Soo. - I see.

264
00:08:27,050 --> 00:08:28,679
There's a famous story about them.

265
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,179
It happened when Sang Min announced his divorce.

266
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,180
That's right.

267
00:08:31,181 --> 00:08:34,119
(Sang Min's press conference on his divorce on September 22, 2006.)

268
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,220
"Now, say a word."

269
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:37,589
What do you think about that?

270
00:08:37,590 --> 00:08:40,190
To be honest, whenever I see Sang Min,

271
00:08:40,260 --> 00:08:41,629
- I feel apologetic toward him. - Oh, my.

272
00:08:41,630 --> 00:08:43,299
- Why? - I always feel bad.

273
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:46,400
And I have to carry the burden for the rest of my life.

274
00:08:46,570 --> 00:08:48,999
It's because Min Soo, who Sang Min calls a big brother,

275
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,970
often shows up at places that he's not supposed to.

276
00:08:52,770 --> 00:08:55,169
He often attends events he's not invited to.

277
00:08:55,170 --> 00:08:57,079
It should be the other way around.

278
00:08:57,080 --> 00:09:01,380
It was a very important time in Sang Min's life.

279
00:09:01,650 --> 00:09:03,519
Why would he show up there?

280
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:05,349
- What a coincidence. - Exactly.

281
00:09:05,350 --> 00:09:06,950
Did you find out from the news articles?

282
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:09,689
I found out what happened from the news articles.

283
00:09:09,690 --> 00:09:13,389
He was riding his motorcycle without a destination.

284
00:09:13,390 --> 00:09:17,059
- Then he saw reporters he knew. - He saw reporters.

285
00:09:17,060 --> 00:09:19,530
The reporters said hello to him.

286
00:09:19,670 --> 00:09:21,929
So he stopped his motorcycle in front of them...

287
00:09:21,930 --> 00:09:23,569
and inquired after them.

288
00:09:23,570 --> 00:09:24,699
And then the reporters...

289
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:27,240
- They escorted him. - escorted him to the venue.

290
00:09:27,410 --> 00:09:29,779
- "Where are you taking me?" - To Sang Min's press conference.

291
00:09:29,780 --> 00:09:32,009
- Yes. He asked where he was going. - Yes.

292
00:09:32,010 --> 00:09:33,379
- No way. - He agreed to follow them.

293
00:09:33,380 --> 00:09:35,579
- Right. - They all made way for him...

294
00:09:35,580 --> 00:09:36,780
to the inside of the room.

295
00:09:37,050 --> 00:09:39,019
Min Soo had no idea where he was going.

296
00:09:39,020 --> 00:09:40,889
When he went inside the venue,

297
00:09:40,890 --> 00:09:42,389
Sang Min wasn't even there.

298
00:09:42,390 --> 00:09:45,190
And Min Soo was seated at the table in the front.

299
00:09:45,860 --> 00:09:49,629
- He wasn't even wearing a suit. - He was in a biker outfit.

300
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:50,829
- He was in a biker outfit. - A biker outfit. Right.

301
00:09:50,830 --> 00:09:52,969
- With a bandana, sunglasses, - And sunglasses.

302
00:09:52,970 --> 00:09:55,170
And a lot of accessories including earrings.

303
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:56,899
While being seated, he asked...

304
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:59,670
what the event was about.

305
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:02,279
- You mean, the press conference. - What it was about.

306
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:05,510
He had no idea what was going to happen there.

307
00:10:05,610 --> 00:10:08,109
While Min Soo was sitting at the table,

308
00:10:08,110 --> 00:10:10,379
he was told about the situation...

309
00:10:10,380 --> 00:10:11,920
from those who were in the room.

310
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:13,496
He told the reporters that it wasn't right...

311
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:15,790
of them to meddle in Sang Min's personal affair.

312
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:17,389
He said it was wrong of them.

313
00:10:17,390 --> 00:10:19,230
While he was lecturing the reporters,

314
00:10:19,490 --> 00:10:21,829
- Sang Min came in, I think. - He spoke for Sang Min.

315
00:10:21,830 --> 00:10:23,099
Sang Min, how did you feel? Be honest with us.

316
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:24,999
Did you not know he was there?

317
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,829
- Of course, I had no idea. - How would he have known?

318
00:10:27,830 --> 00:10:29,846
- It wasn't to announce my divorce. - He held a press conference.

319
00:10:29,870 --> 00:10:32,509
- I needed to explain myself. - Right.

320
00:10:32,510 --> 00:10:33,970
So I entered the room.

321
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:37,139
Let's say this is the seat I was supposed to sit in.

322
00:10:37,140 --> 00:10:38,339
(Min Soo was sitting in his seat.)

323
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:39,879
Min Soo was sitting right here.

324
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:41,560
When he saw me entering the room, he said,

325
00:10:41,650 --> 00:10:42,780
"Come on in."

326
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,579
(Come on in.)

327
00:10:44,580 --> 00:10:46,020
Imagine that Choi Min Soo was there.

328
00:10:47,420 --> 00:10:50,190
How did that happen? The timing was so weird, right?

329
00:10:50,520 --> 00:10:51,659
It sounds like a prank video.

330
00:10:51,660 --> 00:10:53,590
I was even more dumbfounded when he said,

331
00:10:53,730 --> 00:10:54,860
"I heard everything."

332
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:57,800
"Turn your cameras toward me, please."

333
00:10:58,300 --> 00:10:59,860
"Sang Min, you shouldn't be like this."

334
00:11:00,330 --> 00:11:03,800
"Meet her again and try to make things work."

335
00:11:04,740 --> 00:11:06,986
- I mean, he said that... - "You shouldn't be like this."

336
00:11:07,010 --> 00:11:08,439
- He said that... - "You shouldn't be like this."

337
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:10,639
"Meet her again and fall in love again?"

338
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:11,739
(The advice filled with the big brother's love)

339
00:11:11,740 --> 00:11:13,349
- He made a well-wishing remark. - But...

340
00:11:13,350 --> 00:11:15,480
- That's why I always feel bad. - That was so funny.

341
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:18,549
And that's why I really wanted to see Sang Min here.

342
00:11:18,550 --> 00:11:20,519
Sang Min, I'm always sorry.

343
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:23,190
- You know I'm always sorry, right? - But... Yes, I know.

344
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,019
It seems that you guys have a lot to say here.

345
00:11:25,020 --> 00:11:26,259
Didn't you bring anything for us?

346
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:28,730
- Oh, I forgot. - He's carrying a backpack.

347
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:30,929
- He didn't bring a Doraemon bag. - Exactly.

348
00:11:30,930 --> 00:11:33,029
This isn't what I brought from home.

349
00:11:33,030 --> 00:11:35,969
I'm getting ready to pass on my Doraemon merchandise to my son.

350
00:11:35,970 --> 00:11:38,050
- You do have Doraemon bags at home. - Okay. Thanks.

351
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:39,940
- Right? - Are you a fake fan of Doraemon?

352
00:11:40,210 --> 00:11:41,969
- You show off what you have on TV, - Right. It's only for TV shows.

353
00:11:41,970 --> 00:11:44,486
- but you don't cherish them? - He doesn't actually like Doraemon.

354
00:11:44,510 --> 00:11:46,726
- Why didn't you bring it? - His facial expression changed.

355
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:47,809
That's not true.

356
00:11:47,810 --> 00:11:49,026
(Don't doubt my love for Doraemon.)

357
00:11:49,050 --> 00:11:52,049
- You can have a seat now. - Here's their transfer form.

358
00:11:52,050 --> 00:11:54,449
June Kang, Shim Hyung Tak, and Park Joo Ho!

359
00:11:54,450 --> 00:11:55,489
(Names: June Kang, Shim Hyung Tak, Park Joo Ho)

360
00:11:55,490 --> 00:11:57,189
- Welcome! - I really like them.

361
00:11:57,190 --> 00:12:01,130
We'll talk about the topic "The first encounter."

362
00:12:01,290 --> 00:12:02,900
First up is June.

363
00:12:03,260 --> 00:12:05,029
- You won the Canada regional round. - That's right.

364
00:12:05,030 --> 00:12:07,930
The marriage between a popular actor and a Miss Korea contestant...

365
00:12:08,130 --> 00:12:10,369
- was famous when we were younger. - It's so famous.

366
00:12:10,370 --> 00:12:12,069
- Over the phone... - It drew a lot of attention.

367
00:12:12,070 --> 00:12:14,270
- It was 1993. - Oh, my.

368
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:17,679
In 1993, I came to Korea as the winner...

369
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:18,979
of the regional round of Canada.

370
00:12:18,980 --> 00:12:21,149
You said earlier that you had been telling the same story...

371
00:12:21,150 --> 00:12:22,449
- for two years. - Yes.

372
00:12:22,450 --> 00:12:24,049
I've been doing that for 30 years.

373
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:26,420
(I've been doing that for 30 years.)

374
00:12:26,790 --> 00:12:28,489
(I have a long way to go.)

375
00:12:28,490 --> 00:12:31,059
Even so, so many people still don't know the story.

376
00:12:31,060 --> 00:12:33,689
- Their story is always fun to hear. - Earlier on...

377
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:35,929
I've been telling the same story for so many years.

378
00:12:35,930 --> 00:12:37,999
The story about their love that transcended borders...

379
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,699
- was the talk of the town. - Right.

380
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:42,340
As far as I remember, you two met when you went for a tour...

381
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:44,939
- around the MBC building. - That's right.

382
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:46,746
- Yes. Here's how we met. - So you met him in that building.

383
00:12:46,770 --> 00:12:48,409
We first met on the stage...

384
00:12:48,410 --> 00:12:50,039
- of Miss Korea. - At the Miss Korea contest.

385
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:51,379
- At the contest? - So we first met...

386
00:12:51,380 --> 00:12:53,479
- on the stage. - At the contest.

387
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:55,049
How would I have known?

388
00:12:55,050 --> 00:12:56,779
How would I have known this man?

389
00:12:56,780 --> 00:12:58,849
- Growing up in Canada, - Of course, you didn't know.

390
00:12:58,850 --> 00:13:02,019
I never watched any Korean TV shows.

391
00:13:02,020 --> 00:13:04,559
- There were no streaming services. - Exactly.

392
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:08,360
It was the day of the rehearsal.

393
00:13:08,530 --> 00:13:11,030
He showed up for the rehearsal.

394
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:15,499
- There were 51 contestants. - That's a lot.

395
00:13:15,500 --> 00:13:17,040
The other contestants went wild.

396
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:19,309
I didn't know who he was,

397
00:13:19,310 --> 00:13:22,440
but I could tell he was very cool and successful.

398
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:23,909
- He had that kind of aura. - Right.

399
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:25,040
"I am cool."

400
00:13:25,210 --> 00:13:27,979
He walked across the stage,

401
00:13:27,980 --> 00:13:29,680
and all the other ladies whispered,

402
00:13:29,980 --> 00:13:31,419
- "Oh, that's him." - They must've been excited.

403
00:13:31,420 --> 00:13:33,719
- They must've screamed too. - So I kept watching him.

404
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:35,960
And he seemed to try hard to look cool.

405
00:13:36,790 --> 00:13:38,389
- He must've acted so cool then. - Right.

406
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:40,059
- Yes. Right. - Yes. That's for sure.

407
00:13:40,060 --> 00:13:42,660
I could just see how hard he tried to look cool.

408
00:13:42,730 --> 00:13:46,770
That day, I was proud of myself because I won an award.

409
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:48,300
As I was leaving the stage,

410
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:50,470
I saw him on the stage...

411
00:13:50,570 --> 00:13:52,670
- in a suit designed by Andre Kim. - Right.

412
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:54,169
- I didn't even know him then. - I remember that.

413
00:13:54,170 --> 00:13:56,779
He was wearing a very flashy tuxedo,

414
00:13:56,780 --> 00:13:58,480
testing the microphone.

415
00:13:58,610 --> 00:14:00,279
And as soon as he saw me,

416
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:03,179
he said, "Good job," reaching out for a handshake.

417
00:14:03,180 --> 00:14:04,749
So we shook hands.

418
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:06,489
I was down the stage while he was on it.

419
00:14:06,490 --> 00:14:08,819
I said the same thing and left.

420
00:14:08,820 --> 00:14:10,419
And he could tell...

421
00:14:10,420 --> 00:14:12,590
that I didn't recognize him.

422
00:14:13,290 --> 00:14:15,189
He could tell that I didn't know him.

423
00:14:15,190 --> 00:14:17,399
- He must've figured it out. - Yes. He figured it out.

424
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:19,570
So I left after we met.

425
00:14:19,730 --> 00:14:23,199
A week later, on the day before I left for Canada,

426
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:25,540
I was invited to the MBC building...

427
00:14:25,710 --> 00:14:27,739
by the director of the show.

428
00:14:27,740 --> 00:14:29,839
The director offered to give me a tour around the building...

429
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:31,539
before I went back to Canada.

430
00:14:31,540 --> 00:14:34,049
- He offered to give you a tour? - That's right.

431
00:14:34,050 --> 00:14:36,919
The drama called "Mother's Sea..."

432
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:38,749
- was being filmed... - It was aired around the time.

433
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:40,019
- at the time. - It was aired then. Right.

434
00:14:40,020 --> 00:14:42,620
The director introduced me to Min Soo behind the set.

435
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:45,759
"Min Soo, one of the contestants of Miss Korea..."

436
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:47,829
"who came really far from Korea is here."

437
00:14:47,830 --> 00:14:49,359
"Let me introduce her to you."

438
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:52,570
But Min Soo didn't look at me.

439
00:14:52,830 --> 00:14:55,469
He just fiddled with his hair.

440
00:14:55,470 --> 00:14:57,799
I reached out my hand,

441
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,569
and he saw my hand.

442
00:14:59,570 --> 00:15:00,839
Then he finally looked at me.

443
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:04,679
He asked me if I was the one whom he met...

444
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:06,250
- at the contest. - He remembered her.

445
00:15:06,580 --> 00:15:07,980
And we parted ways there.

446
00:15:08,350 --> 00:15:10,349
I asked the director...

447
00:15:10,350 --> 00:15:13,690
if he could get Min Soo's autograph for me.

448
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:16,820
He said he'd ask if Min Soo was there when we left the studio.

449
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:19,429
When we came out, Min Soo was...

450
00:15:19,430 --> 00:15:21,830
doing an interview with some reporters.

451
00:15:22,030 --> 00:15:24,130
So I went up to him and asked...

452
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:26,330
if I could get his autograph.

453
00:15:26,430 --> 00:15:28,430
And then Min Soo...

454
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:31,369
asked me to go somewhere to have some coffee with him.

455
00:15:31,370 --> 00:15:33,770
There was a cafe in the MBC building.

456
00:15:33,840 --> 00:15:36,039
We had coffee at the cafe.

457
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:38,409
But my Korean was not very good.

458
00:15:38,410 --> 00:15:39,709
I spoke broken Korean,

459
00:15:39,710 --> 00:15:41,210
and he spoke broken English.

460
00:15:41,380 --> 00:15:43,580
- So we talked to each other. - "Broken Korean?"

461
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:47,520
Three hours later, he held my hand and said,

462
00:15:47,850 --> 00:15:51,120
"I'd like to propose to you."

463
00:15:51,220 --> 00:15:52,319
That quickly?

464
00:15:52,320 --> 00:15:54,160
- Only three hours later? - Three hours later?

465
00:15:55,060 --> 00:15:57,606
He proposed to you after talking to you with his broken English?

466
00:15:57,630 --> 00:15:59,699
He must've felt some kind of supernatural energy.

467
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:03,739
Right. We spent three hours together at the cafe.

468
00:16:03,740 --> 00:16:05,940
He delayed the shoot because of me.

469
00:16:06,210 --> 00:16:08,269
He walked around in the building,

470
00:16:08,270 --> 00:16:10,340
- holding my hand. - Right. Of course.

471
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:13,609
People we ran into asked him if I was his wife.

472
00:16:13,610 --> 00:16:16,119
I thought to myself, "That's not my name."

473
00:16:16,120 --> 00:16:18,480
- "Why does everyone say that?" - You didn't know the word.

474
00:16:19,020 --> 00:16:20,319
- Kang Hyung Soo. - "Hyung Soo."

475
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,549
- K.Will's real name is Hyung Soo. - If she didn't know the word...

476
00:16:21,550 --> 00:16:23,759
- I thought people confused me... - With some other girl?

477
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:25,596
- with some other woman. - That's what she must've thought.

478
00:16:25,620 --> 00:16:26,859
- Not K.Will, though. - Because that wasn't my name.

479
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:28,930
I was 23 years old then.

480
00:16:29,260 --> 00:16:32,299
And I had one semester left to graduate college.

481
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:34,869
So he was holding my hand,

482
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:38,440
and I thought that he was so famous...

483
00:16:38,940 --> 00:16:42,640
- that he held every woman's hand. - That's possible.

484
00:16:43,410 --> 00:16:44,609
You thought he was a playboy.

485
00:16:44,610 --> 00:16:46,880
That thought crossed my mind for a brief moment.

486
00:16:47,010 --> 00:16:49,550
Also, I looked into his eyes,

487
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:52,490
and I had this feeling that I would see those eyes...

488
00:16:52,650 --> 00:16:56,260
for the rest of my life at that moment.

489
00:16:56,660 --> 00:16:57,920
It gave me goosebumps.

490
00:16:58,190 --> 00:16:59,710
I couldn't even describe that feeling.

491
00:16:59,830 --> 00:17:01,529
But I didn't think it was right.

492
00:17:01,530 --> 00:17:03,029
I didn't think it was possible.

493
00:17:03,030 --> 00:17:04,359
I didn't think...

494
00:17:04,360 --> 00:17:06,929
I could give up my life in Canada and move to Korea.

495
00:17:06,930 --> 00:17:10,100
So I decided to leave it behind as a good memory.

496
00:17:10,340 --> 00:17:14,339
Min Soo gave me about five different phone numbers.

497
00:17:14,340 --> 00:17:16,739
- He asked me to call him... - He must've fallen hard for her.

498
00:17:16,740 --> 00:17:18,100
Before leaving the day after that.

499
00:17:18,140 --> 00:17:20,049
- But I didn't call him. - Right. I remember the story.

500
00:17:20,050 --> 00:17:21,109
- Gosh. - Oh, no.

501
00:17:21,110 --> 00:17:23,179
So I was at the Gimpo International Airport.

502
00:17:23,180 --> 00:17:25,649
On the day of leaving Korea, at the Gimpo International Airport,

503
00:17:25,650 --> 00:17:27,149
- He must've come to see her. - I was having naengmyeon...

504
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:29,219
with my family on the second floor.

505
00:17:29,220 --> 00:17:30,719
- We were going to say goodbye. - I see.

506
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,859
But then, there was a man coming to us from far.

507
00:17:32,860 --> 00:17:34,429
He was wearing sunglasses...

508
00:17:34,430 --> 00:17:36,299
- and had this hat on. Right. - Anyone can tell it's Min Soo.

509
00:17:36,300 --> 00:17:37,399
- So... - Seriously.

510
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:40,500
Don't you think this story is just perfect for Min Soo?

511
00:17:40,530 --> 00:17:42,669
So he was coming up.

512
00:17:42,670 --> 00:17:44,039
- He didn't go to his schedule. - I was looking down, thinking,

513
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,400
"Goodness. It can't be."

514
00:17:45,540 --> 00:17:47,669
"Did he really come all the way here? It can't be."

515
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:49,879
But it seemed like it was him.

516
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:52,680
I was standing at the end of the escalator when he suddenly said,

517
00:17:52,780 --> 00:17:57,650
"June, I asked you to call me. Why didn't you give me a call?"

518
00:17:57,820 --> 00:18:00,266
He said he came all the way there because he was so concerned.

519
00:18:00,290 --> 00:18:01,290
- Did he say that... - So...

520
00:18:01,291 --> 00:18:02,466
- with his broken English? - Well...

521
00:18:02,490 --> 00:18:05,059
- "Hey, June! Call me." - He said everything in Korean.

522
00:18:05,060 --> 00:18:07,160
- "Call back. Why not call back?" - He had this...

523
00:18:08,730 --> 00:18:12,970
He brought this box in which he put...

524
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:16,599
all his photos all night. And on the backs of these photos...

525
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:18,999
- There was no social media then. - Right.

526
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:21,539
He wrote all the stories...

527
00:18:21,540 --> 00:18:24,139
- from his life there. - His stories.

528
00:18:24,140 --> 00:18:26,910
- He wrote his stories there. - Stories to introduce himself.

529
00:18:27,010 --> 00:18:29,579
As he handed me the box,

530
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:31,049
he gave me this letter that said,

531
00:18:31,050 --> 00:18:33,350
"This is our birthday."

532
00:18:33,650 --> 00:18:39,190
"Can you live your life for me from this day forth, June?"

533
00:18:39,530 --> 00:18:40,830
He wrote that in the letter.

534
00:18:41,190 --> 00:18:43,929
And it creeped me out.

535
00:18:43,930 --> 00:18:45,560
I mean...

536
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:47,869
- What is that? - It was all too fast.

537
00:18:47,870 --> 00:18:49,299
- It was like a threat. - She would have thought,

538
00:18:49,300 --> 00:18:50,699
- "Is this what celebrities like?" - "Can you live your life for me?"

539
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:52,639
- Living my life for someone else? - She must've been scared at first.

540
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:53,669
- I was only 23 years old. - Right.

541
00:18:53,670 --> 00:18:55,709
I didn't even know who I was back then.

542
00:18:55,710 --> 00:18:57,839
So he wrote this letter...

543
00:18:57,840 --> 00:19:00,550
- and gave it to me. - My gosh.

544
00:19:00,650 --> 00:19:03,420
After we parted at the airport that day, he came to Canada...

545
00:19:04,150 --> 00:19:06,919
four times. Every weekend in a row.

546
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:08,949
He shot a drama during weekdays.

547
00:19:08,950 --> 00:19:13,130
And he flew for 17 hours on weekends to Canada.

548
00:19:13,260 --> 00:19:14,589
- And then he flew back to Seoul. - That's really amazing.

549
00:19:14,590 --> 00:19:15,999
He did that four times in a row.

550
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:18,030
- That's unbelievable. - I know.

551
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:21,769
Listening to their story so far reminds me of this.

552
00:19:21,770 --> 00:19:24,969
A drama that Min Soo starred in that we watched when we were young.

553
00:19:24,970 --> 00:19:26,169
It's like "Sandglass."

554
00:19:26,170 --> 00:19:28,209
- It's like a story from his drama. - That's right.

555
00:19:28,210 --> 00:19:30,209
- The story and characters are... - The leading role.

556
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:32,709
It's just like a story in which Min Soo plays the leading role.

557
00:19:32,710 --> 00:19:34,579
There's one more thing to add.

558
00:19:34,580 --> 00:19:37,849
- When he arrived at the airport... - Right.

559
00:19:37,850 --> 00:19:41,149
Andre Kim sponsored a lot of clothes...

560
00:19:41,150 --> 00:19:43,619
- at that time. - Right. Andre Kim.

561
00:19:43,620 --> 00:19:45,719
- He came in those clothes? - When he arrived...

562
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:49,430
When I saw him arrive at the airport from far...

563
00:19:50,260 --> 00:19:52,499
He was standing out too much.

564
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:53,769
Was he wearing Andre Kim's clothes?

565
00:19:53,770 --> 00:19:56,069
- Andre Kim's clothes are... - They are so fancy.

566
00:19:56,070 --> 00:19:58,100
- Seriously? - His clothes are...

567
00:19:59,370 --> 00:20:00,869
Do you know how fancy they are?

568
00:20:00,870 --> 00:20:02,409
- They're so fancy. - Right?

569
00:20:02,410 --> 00:20:04,739
- The logo represented the clothes. - The logo?

570
00:20:04,740 --> 00:20:06,279
He wore one of those clothes from fashion shows?

571
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:08,979
- There was this logo. - He took a 17-hour flight in them?

572
00:20:08,980 --> 00:20:12,720
- Right. With this huge golden logo. - I know.

573
00:20:12,890 --> 00:20:14,289
I was flustered.

574
00:20:14,290 --> 00:20:16,559
With his long coat...

575
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:19,189
When he took off his coat at my house,

576
00:20:19,190 --> 00:20:21,960
he had on his suit with the same logo.

577
00:20:22,390 --> 00:20:23,859
When he took off his jacket,

578
00:20:23,860 --> 00:20:26,069
there was a vest with the same logo.

579
00:20:26,070 --> 00:20:28,799
Hold on. How long will this go on?

580
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:29,900
(There are endless logos.)

581
00:20:30,070 --> 00:20:32,169
When he took off that vest,

582
00:20:32,170 --> 00:20:35,569
- his shirt had that logo too. - He's so amazing.

583
00:20:35,570 --> 00:20:37,079
- Even his shirt. - That's unbelievable.

584
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:39,679
- That's a full package. - He had about five layers...

585
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:41,149
- of Andre Kim's clothes. - Gosh.

586
00:20:41,150 --> 00:20:43,779
That was when he came to Canada for the first time.

587
00:20:43,780 --> 00:20:45,649
(Min Soo's first arrival was quite impressive.)

588
00:20:45,650 --> 00:20:46,950
My gosh.

589
00:20:47,320 --> 00:20:48,749
How about your parents?

590
00:20:48,750 --> 00:20:50,759
When Min Soo visited Canada so frequently,

591
00:20:50,760 --> 00:20:53,189
- did they approve of him? - The thing is...

592
00:20:53,190 --> 00:20:54,659
I was an only child for them.

593
00:20:54,660 --> 00:20:56,599
For my parents,

594
00:20:56,600 --> 00:21:00,200
if there had been any man who would have asked me to marry,

595
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:02,369
it would have been a really tough situation for them.

596
00:21:02,370 --> 00:21:04,569
I always thought about this.

597
00:21:04,570 --> 00:21:07,870
I thought it might be impossible for me...

598
00:21:07,970 --> 00:21:10,210
to marry a Korean guy.

599
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:12,139
- And I think... - There was a cultural difference.

600
00:21:12,140 --> 00:21:15,709
That's what my parents had in mind back then.

601
00:21:15,710 --> 00:21:20,050
And then they met this very traditional Korean guy.

602
00:21:20,420 --> 00:21:24,059
A traditional Korean man who should have been born 200 years ago.

603
00:21:24,060 --> 00:21:25,559
(A man who was born in the wrong era)

604
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:27,289
- Isn't that right? - Right.

605
00:21:27,290 --> 00:21:29,159
- Seriously. - That was spot on.

606
00:21:29,160 --> 00:21:31,359
- You know what I mean, right? - Like a general from the old days.

607
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:33,029
He was like the character from "Highlander."

608
00:21:33,030 --> 00:21:35,830
He was born at the wrong time.

609
00:21:36,030 --> 00:21:39,669
Right? I met this guy who should've been born 200 years ago.

610
00:21:39,670 --> 00:21:42,409
The scene of my parents...

611
00:21:42,410 --> 00:21:44,809
talking to him...

612
00:21:44,810 --> 00:21:47,180
It was something I couldn't imagine.

613
00:21:47,950 --> 00:21:50,949
Also, Min Soo and my parents...

614
00:21:50,950 --> 00:21:52,579
- got along so well. - He did?

615
00:21:52,580 --> 00:21:54,849
My parents were enjoying his company,

616
00:21:54,850 --> 00:21:57,420
and they looked so happy. As I was watching them...

617
00:21:57,760 --> 00:21:59,419
"Gosh, I can't believe this is happening."

618
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:01,829
"How could they accept him like this?"

619
00:22:01,830 --> 00:22:03,859
I have a question. According to what you just said...

620
00:22:03,860 --> 00:22:05,599
It sounded like your parents said yes,

621
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:08,069
- but you didn't yet? - I wasn't... Right.

622
00:22:08,070 --> 00:22:12,400
I didn't have a chance to say yes.

623
00:22:12,670 --> 00:22:15,269
Things just happened so suddenly.

624
00:22:15,270 --> 00:22:17,639
I was at the wedding hall all of a sudden.

625
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:19,239
I saw him and thought,

626
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:23,879
"I guess it's a little late to tell him no."

627
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:25,820
- Gosh. - That's what you thought?

628
00:22:25,980 --> 00:22:29,789
There were so many people that I didn't know at the church.

629
00:22:29,790 --> 00:22:33,030
So then, I had so many thoughts in my head.

630
00:22:33,190 --> 00:22:35,829
"How did things turn out like this?"

631
00:22:35,830 --> 00:22:36,999
That's what I thought.

632
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:40,569
- So that's what happened. - Then I want to ask what was...

633
00:22:40,570 --> 00:22:42,429
- You got married at 23. - I got married then.

634
00:22:42,430 --> 00:22:43,669
You were so young then.

635
00:22:43,670 --> 00:22:45,739
What was the ideal type of man...

636
00:22:45,740 --> 00:22:48,369
that you wanted back then?

637
00:22:48,370 --> 00:22:50,909
- Well, it's... - Compared to Min Soo.

638
00:22:50,910 --> 00:22:52,580
It wasn't him.

639
00:22:53,380 --> 00:22:54,849
- So it wasn't him. - He's different.

640
00:22:54,850 --> 00:22:56,919
- It wasn't him. - Your ideal type wasn't him.

641
00:22:56,920 --> 00:22:58,419
- My ideal type of man was... - So it wasn't him.

642
00:22:58,420 --> 00:23:00,920
I didn't want someone who had a strong personality.

643
00:23:01,220 --> 00:23:02,959
I wanted to meet...

644
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:05,959
someone calm and who studied while focused.

645
00:23:05,960 --> 00:23:08,029
That was the type of man...

646
00:23:08,030 --> 00:23:10,859
- Like an adorable dork? - I liked back then.

647
00:23:10,860 --> 00:23:12,559
- I see. - But...

648
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:14,769
- he's someone I couldn't imagine. - He's the polar opposite.

649
00:23:14,770 --> 00:23:16,769
- That's who I got married to. - He's a man from 200 years ago.

650
00:23:16,770 --> 00:23:18,469
Right. A man from 200 years ago.

651
00:23:18,470 --> 00:23:20,239
This is just like, "Guardian: The Lonely and Great God."

652
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:22,169
- Gosh, from 200 years ago. - A man from 200 years ago.

653
00:23:22,170 --> 00:23:23,809
- Hyung Tak, you like this story? - Next.

654
00:23:23,810 --> 00:23:25,709
- Let's listen to Hyung Tak. - Next is Hyung Tak...

655
00:23:25,710 --> 00:23:27,549
- who worried so much. - Right.

656
00:23:27,550 --> 00:23:29,590
About your first meeting with your wife, you wrote,

657
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:32,380
"An accident while digging?" What do you mean?

658
00:23:32,580 --> 00:23:34,519
- "An accident while digging." Yes. - You were digging something?

659
00:23:34,520 --> 00:23:36,219
I went to shoot a show called...

660
00:23:36,220 --> 00:23:38,159
- "Nanaland." - "Nanaland."

661
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:40,290
This was the purpose of this show.

662
00:23:40,430 --> 00:23:42,929
It was to let people know about geek culture.

663
00:23:42,930 --> 00:23:44,259
It was a show for that.

664
00:23:44,260 --> 00:23:46,129
- So there were geeks on the show. - Right.

665
00:23:46,130 --> 00:23:49,500
- They asked me to join the show... - I see.

666
00:23:49,770 --> 00:23:52,399
As a geek who represented Korea.

667
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:54,239
So I accepted the offer.

668
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:57,640
That night, I was sleeping,

669
00:23:58,010 --> 00:24:01,779
I had this dream. There were five dragons flying in the sky.

670
00:24:01,780 --> 00:24:05,149
- Goodness. - Then the dragons turned around...

671
00:24:05,150 --> 00:24:08,649
and became a one big dragon, and it charged toward me.

672
00:24:08,650 --> 00:24:10,819
I woke up as it came into me.

673
00:24:10,820 --> 00:24:12,489
- Isn't that a conception dream? - It sounds like a conception dream.

674
00:24:12,490 --> 00:24:14,929
- Five dragons become one? - They became one?

675
00:24:14,930 --> 00:24:16,600
Didn't you have morning sickness?

676
00:24:17,130 --> 00:24:19,229
That sounds like a conception dream.

677
00:24:19,230 --> 00:24:20,699
- Hyung Tak. - It sounds like...

678
00:24:20,700 --> 00:24:22,899
you're going to have a king or something.

679
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:24,739
Hyung Tak, so you went to Japan to shoot,

680
00:24:24,740 --> 00:24:26,469
and you were sleeping in Japan.

681
00:24:26,470 --> 00:24:28,209
No. It was before going to Japan for a shoot.

682
00:24:28,210 --> 00:24:29,569
- The day before departure? - My goodness.

683
00:24:29,570 --> 00:24:30,909
- This is amazing. - You had this dream then?

684
00:24:30,910 --> 00:24:34,409
We finished shooting at the Doraemon Museum.

685
00:24:34,410 --> 00:24:38,650
The next day, we went to a robot cafe to shoot an episode.

686
00:24:39,050 --> 00:24:42,889
That day, there was this one person who was in charge of the robot cafe.

687
00:24:42,890 --> 00:24:46,490
To help us shoot the show, she was there.

688
00:24:46,590 --> 00:24:49,590
And I couldn't take my eyes off of her while shooting the show.

689
00:24:49,730 --> 00:24:52,129
- She was so beautiful. My goodness. - Who became your wife.

690
00:24:52,130 --> 00:24:54,470
- Goodness. - So she was the dragon.

691
00:24:54,900 --> 00:24:56,739
"I won't get married if it's not her."

692
00:24:56,740 --> 00:24:57,969
- That's what I thought. - You felt it like that?

693
00:24:57,970 --> 00:25:00,169
That's what I thought while I was shooting the show.

694
00:25:00,170 --> 00:25:01,909
- You meet the one just like that. - I guess you somehow know it.

695
00:25:01,910 --> 00:25:04,709
Right. So when the shoot was over,

696
00:25:04,710 --> 00:25:06,509
when the staff members were having a meal,

697
00:25:06,510 --> 00:25:08,879
I went to her who was standing at the entrance.

698
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:10,949
I wanted to ease the atmosphere...

699
00:25:10,950 --> 00:25:13,920
and wanted her to see me as a funny guy.

700
00:25:14,050 --> 00:25:16,189
So in Japanese, I said,

701
00:25:16,190 --> 00:25:19,489
"I'm a handsome actor from Korea."

702
00:25:19,490 --> 00:25:20,929
"I'm a Korean actor."

703
00:25:20,930 --> 00:25:22,359
- "Handsome guy." - "Handsome guy."

704
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:24,859
- It was broken Japanese. - Right.

705
00:25:24,860 --> 00:25:26,429
- Right. It was broken Japanese. - My goodness.

706
00:25:26,430 --> 00:25:27,899
So the language should be broken...

707
00:25:27,900 --> 00:25:29,846
- for you to get married. - You fall in love when it's broken.

708
00:25:29,870 --> 00:25:32,469
So when I said that, her face looked awkward.

709
00:25:32,470 --> 00:25:33,669
(She had a straight face when she heard him.)

710
00:25:33,670 --> 00:25:35,739
Later, I asked her about it.

711
00:25:35,740 --> 00:25:37,539
She told me that...

712
00:25:37,540 --> 00:25:40,579
she thought I was a serious narcissist.

713
00:25:40,580 --> 00:25:42,009
- I see. - Someone who loves himself.

714
00:25:42,010 --> 00:25:44,319
She said that she didn't like it.

715
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:47,049
So I went to the local coordinator...

716
00:25:47,050 --> 00:25:49,919
and asked if I could get her social network ID.

717
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:52,389
He got it somehow,

718
00:25:52,390 --> 00:25:55,289
and I sent her a message on that day.

719
00:25:55,290 --> 00:25:57,629
"Thank you for your hard work today."

720
00:25:57,630 --> 00:25:59,199
Then she replied back.

721
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:02,229
"You did great today. Did you go back to Korea safely?"

722
00:26:02,230 --> 00:26:04,169
I said, "I did."

723
00:26:04,170 --> 00:26:06,409
And she didn't reply after that.

724
00:26:06,410 --> 00:26:09,069
And the next day, when I got up, I send her messages like,

725
00:26:09,070 --> 00:26:11,939
"I had breakfast. Did you have lunch?"

726
00:26:11,940 --> 00:26:14,749
"Did you have dinner? You did a great job today."

727
00:26:14,750 --> 00:26:16,280
"I'm going out for a shoot."

728
00:26:16,420 --> 00:26:17,880
I kept sending her messages,

729
00:26:18,050 --> 00:26:20,166
but I wouldn't get a reply. She would read and not answer.

730
00:26:20,190 --> 00:26:21,850
She kept reading and not answering.

731
00:26:22,020 --> 00:26:24,089
After that, it went on for about two more weeks.

732
00:26:24,090 --> 00:26:25,759
(He sent her messages for 2 more weeks.)

733
00:26:25,760 --> 00:26:27,329
And then I finally got a reply.

734
00:26:27,330 --> 00:26:29,030
- It came. - I got a reply.

735
00:26:29,390 --> 00:26:32,060
"Do you remember me?" That's what the reply was.

736
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:34,669
As soon as I got it, I said,

737
00:26:34,670 --> 00:26:37,299
"No, I don't remember. So I think I should go to Japan."

738
00:26:37,300 --> 00:26:39,069
- "I'll be right there." - Gosh.

739
00:26:39,070 --> 00:26:41,809
So I went to Japan,

740
00:26:41,810 --> 00:26:43,979
- and that's how we started dating. - Gosh.

741
00:26:43,980 --> 00:26:45,139
That's amazing.

742
00:26:45,140 --> 00:26:46,479
With this story,

743
