794
00:28:27,910 --> 00:28:31,549
But when I held her hand,

795
00:28:31,550 --> 00:28:33,420
she said that she didn't mind it at all.

796
00:28:34,120 --> 00:28:37,389
So she thought I might be a good match,

797
00:28:37,390 --> 00:28:39,259
and she searched online.

798
00:28:39,260 --> 00:28:42,529
She searched my name online to see who I was in Korea.

799
00:28:42,530 --> 00:28:43,830
She kept searching,

800
00:28:44,330 --> 00:28:47,169
and it said that I was a wholesome actor...

801
00:28:47,170 --> 00:28:49,069
and that I was good to my parents.

802
00:28:49,070 --> 00:28:52,000
That's what it said on the news.

803
00:28:52,270 --> 00:28:55,910
So she decided to open up to me after that.

804
00:28:56,140 --> 00:28:59,579
And after that, we had a drink for the first time.

805
00:28:59,580 --> 00:29:01,180
- Two draft beers? - Yes.

806
00:29:02,110 --> 00:29:03,749
- Two. - Yes, two.

807
00:29:03,750 --> 00:29:04,750
- Two. - Two.

808
00:29:04,751 --> 00:29:06,379
- Two draft beers. - Yes.

809
00:29:06,380 --> 00:29:08,319
- Two draft beers. - I understood that.

810
00:29:08,320 --> 00:29:09,449
After all that coffee.

811
00:29:09,450 --> 00:29:10,459
(I understood that.)

812
00:29:10,460 --> 00:29:12,889
So we went for a drink that day,

813
00:29:12,890 --> 00:29:14,559
and I knew it was time.

814
00:29:14,560 --> 00:29:17,299
We went for a drink at 4pm at a Japanese bar...

815
00:29:17,300 --> 00:29:19,229
and kept drinking.

816
00:29:19,230 --> 00:29:21,070
We had draft beers.

817
00:29:21,470 --> 00:29:23,369
I escorted her home in a taxi...

818
00:29:23,370 --> 00:29:25,569
and sent her home.

819
00:29:25,570 --> 00:29:27,086
- Did you have the feeling that day? - Yes.

820
00:29:27,110 --> 00:29:30,040
I sent her home, and she liked that.

821
00:29:30,340 --> 00:29:31,439
She realized what a gentleman I was.

822
00:29:31,440 --> 00:29:34,050
How many times had you gone to Japan at that point?

823
00:29:34,410 --> 00:29:36,719
That was about five months later.

824
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:38,479
- Five months? - Five months? Really?

825
00:29:38,480 --> 00:29:41,019
It's so interesting that you didn't give up for five months.

826
00:29:41,020 --> 00:29:43,319
- That's amazing. - That happens when you're in love.

827
00:29:43,320 --> 00:29:44,990
- It just had to be her. - I know.

828
00:29:45,490 --> 00:29:46,990
So at that time,

829
