946
00:34:04,980 --> 00:34:06,449
- Not at all. It was ruled out. - Sure.

947
00:34:06,450 --> 00:34:07,789
That's possible.

948
00:34:07,790 --> 00:34:08,890
That's how it was,

949
00:34:09,190 --> 00:34:11,059
but after she asked me that,

950
00:34:11,060 --> 00:34:12,419
she was cute,

951
00:34:12,420 --> 00:34:14,129
- and she was pretty. - She's so pretty.

952
00:34:14,130 --> 00:34:15,529
Yes. So that's how...

953
00:34:15,530 --> 00:34:17,129
I asked her out.

954
00:34:17,130 --> 00:34:18,399
- That's how it went. - He likes it.

955
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,859
Look at his smile when he's talking about it.

956
00:34:19,860 --> 00:34:21,499
He liked her first.

957
00:34:21,500 --> 00:34:23,269
- Joo Ho... - He liked her a lot.

958
00:34:23,270 --> 00:34:25,339
- You're right. - But the important thing is that...

959
00:34:25,340 --> 00:34:27,069
Joo Ho probably spoke in broken English back then.

960
00:34:27,070 --> 00:34:29,339
- You're right. - So he wasn't clear about it.

961
00:34:29,340 --> 00:34:30,509
- You're right. - That's right.

962
00:34:30,510 --> 00:34:32,609
So that's how it became a love story.

963
00:34:32,610 --> 00:34:34,209
- You're right. - She didn't catch what he said.

964
00:34:34,210 --> 00:34:36,079
Broken languages bring people together.

965
00:34:36,080 --> 00:34:38,079
- Yes. - Listen.

966
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:40,249
Yeong Cheol is good at English, so it never works out for him.

967
00:34:40,250 --> 00:34:41,250
I should have been bad at it.

968
00:34:41,251 --> 00:34:43,759
- I should have been bad at English. - He is... June.

969
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:45,719
Yeong Cheol is good at both...

970
00:34:45,720 --> 00:34:48,159
- English and Japanese. - I speak English and Japanese.

971
00:34:48,160 --> 00:34:49,789
- That's why it doesn't work. - Sure.

972
00:34:49,790 --> 00:34:52,459
- He is ready to be like Min Soo. - It has to be broken.

973
00:34:52,460 --> 00:34:55,530
- It has to be broken. - We will now study the couples.

974
00:34:55,970 --> 00:34:57,570
I am really curious about this as well.

975
00:34:57,870 --> 00:35:00,339
Is the process for marriage registration different,

976
00:35:00,340 --> 00:35:02,439
- compared to us? - Marriage registration?

977
00:35:02,440 --> 00:35:04,579
- It depends on the country. - How does it differ?

978
00:35:04,580 --> 00:35:06,109
Do you do it in both countries?

979
00:35:06,110 --> 00:35:07,456
- Is that how you do it? - Do you register on both sides?

980
00:35:07,480 --> 00:35:10,349
